cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques for clinical information extraction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models and pre-trained word embeddings, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with clinical data, which could potentially fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
